##Generic drugs are coming. How far is the "wonder drug" Redesivir from Chinese patients?

Wechat, chinanewsweekly

Function introduction, here is "China News weekly" the head of the weekly gentleman, the influence has the influence you. Come with me to break through the fog, to find the truth, to watch the Times.

The epidemic will accelerate the listing of drugs, compassion and other supporting regulations and improve the landing

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As the United States Gilead Company in the research drug, Ridgway Remdisivir recently received global attention, the recent development of a new coronavirus drug also caused a boom in the stock market.

Shares of Jilly rose nearly 20 percent in the U.S. on the news that Ministry of Health of the People's Republic of China had urgently contacted Gilead for a clinical trial starting Feb. 4.

On February 12, the company announced that it had successfully copied and developed the raw material drug synthesis technology and preparation technology of Radicivir, and mass produced the raw material drug of Radicivir, mass production of Radzivir preparations is under way. On the same day, Borui medicine one word up, up 20% , the stock price hit in November 2019 since the listing of the new high, its rise led to a shares of pharmaceutical stocks as a whole higher, better than the market.

When will redcevir be available to patients, becoming the focus of attention for patients with new pneumonia and the whole society.

Generic drugs

On January 31, the Journal The New England Journal of Medicine published a paper detailing the first U.S. case of a treatment for new coronary pneumonia with Redoxivir.

Industry experts believe that a single case can not determine whether a patient's improvement is related to the use of Radzivir, and acute viral infections are usually self-limiting. As a broad spectrum antiviral drug, the drug has yet to be approved for sale in any country in the world because of its poor results in Phase III trials for Zaire ebolavirus. Therefore, whether Radzivir is a "wonder drug" or not, we need to wait for the data of clinical studies to verify its inhibitory effect on the new coronavirus.

The dependence on patent in medicine field is very strong, before the medicine goes on the market, the medicine enterprise must be equipped with the omni-directional patent protection to be able to safely push it into the market.

Founded in 1987, Gilead Patents are distributed all over the world, with the United States, Europe, Japan, Australia, Canada and other developed countries and regions densest, but also widely distributed in developing countries, is now the dominant player in the field of anti-virus. "Gilead is less like a traditional pharmaceutical company and more like a high-tech company in Silicon Valley, " said Luo Yongqing, Global Vice President and general manager of Gilead Sciences in China.

On Feb. 13, Borui medicine issued a notice of abnormal stock trading fluctuations, said the company concerned about media reports or market rumors, the company's development of Red Xiwei suspected of patent infringement. So far, the company's research and development work on Ridgway is still in the R & D Phase, the company does not believe that the above-mentioned R & D issues in the case of patent infringement.

If the clinical trial of Ridgeville does not turn out well, the imitative technique is of little value, boorujy warns. Even if the trial is successful, product Marketing Requires Gilead authorization, drug clinical, approval and other links, the process will be a major uncertainty.

So, whether can our Country Pharmacy Enterprise carry on imitation to Red Xiwei at present?

Generic drugs are drugs with the same active ingredients, dosage forms, administration routes and therapeutic effects as the original research drugs. The State Council General Office recently issued an opinion on the evaluation of the quality and efficacy of generic drugs, which requires the approval of generic drugs before the implementation of the new registration and classification of chemicals, consistency evaluation must be carried out for those who fail to be approved in accordance with the principle of consistency with the quality and efficacy of the original drug. Conformity Assessment of quality and efficacy requires that generic drugs that have been approved for the market be consistent with the original drug in quality and efficacy and can be replaced by the original drug in clinical practice, this is conducive to saving society's medical costs.

Li Ruifeng, project director and senior patent agent of Longtian Intellectual Property Operation (Shenzhen) Co. , Ltd. , told China News Weekly, although patents for coronavirus indications have not yet been licensed by the State Intellectual Property Office in China, the structure of the drug makes a difference. "since its core patent for chemical combination is authorized and valid in China, it is a patent infringement to manufacture, use, promise to sell, sell or import its patented products without the permission of the patentee under Article 60 of China's patent law. As a result, Chinese drug companies need a license from Gilead to produce the structure."

Li Ruifeng pointed out that at present, China's pharmaceutical companies are not yet able to make a generic drug declaration against Redesavir, but at this stage, China's pharmaceutical companies can start to prepare for "imitation, " as in the 2005 influenza outbreak, to avoid compulsory licensing of patents, Roche voluntarily allowed the Shangyao group to produce Oseltamivir in the event of a possible flu pandemic, and then licensed it to Eastsun.

Sympathetic medication

On February 1, a National Health Board panel said it had contacted Gilead to introduce Ridgeville and apply for green passage for the company. On February 2, the website of the Drug Review Center of the State Drug Administration showed that the application for clinical trial of Radzivir in China has been accepted.

According to a report by the Xinhua News Agency, Radzivir has entered the phase III clinical trial directly in China. A total of 761 patients with new pneumonia will join the trial group, the trial will be carried out in a number of first-line hospitals, including Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital, where the first batch of patients with severe new pneumonia received the drug on February 6.

On February 13, the State Intellectual Property Office held a meeting of the party group and the Bureau's Leading Group on the new pneumonia epidemic, which stressed the need to actively support enterprises to resume production and start construction of new projects, we will open up a "green channel" for the application for registration of patents and trademarks related to the prevention and treatment of new pneumonia in enterprises that resume work and production and in new construction projects, and speed up the processing efficiency; we will guide and support enterprises in using intellectual property rights to carry out pledge financing, eASE financial difficulties.

According to Zhang Fang, a partner at the law firm Kejie, innovative drugs go through pre-clinical research, Phase I, Phase II and Phase III clinical trials, as well as market production approval procedures, according to the general drug listing procedures, it could take years or even decades. Even if, as with Ridgeville, it takes months or years to complete the clinical trial and production approval process, it is important to speed up the drug's rollout through special procedures.

The special chapter of the measures for the administration of Drug Registration (draft for soliciting opinions) issued by the State General Administration of Market Supervision and administration on December 10,2019 provides for procedures for speeding up the listing of drugs, there are four procedures: special approval, conditional approval, priority review approval and breakthrough treatment drugs, and this outbreak clearly constitutes a typical scenario for its application.

Regarding the timing of Ridgway's official entry into the Chinese market, Li said that if the risks of the clinical trial were to benefit significantly, a listing application for the strain could presumably be approved as soon as June. Although the State Food and Drug Administration has accelerated the approval process, it has not lowered the evaluation criteria, and the final approval will be based on a comprehensive evaluation of the safety and effectiveness data obtained.

It is worth noting that, in addition to joining clinical trials to gain access to the drug, another possible approach for patients who are in urgent need of Radcivir is compassionate use, which originated in the United States, it refers to the use of drugs in clinical trials for patients who are not involved in clinical trials under special circumstances. Ridgeville is not yet available globally, and patients in the United States are treated with a compassionate drug.

Gilead said that in response to the Ebola outbreak, Gilead has expanded production of Ridgeville and increased its stock of raw materials to meet the need for compassionate use and clinical trials in China, capacity is being replenished through in-house manufacturing and external partnerships.

So, can China also use sympathetic medication to treat patients with new coronary pneumonia?

Zhang pointed out that China's current effective laws and regulations also have provisions on compassionate use of drugs, but both the new drug law and the Good Clinical Practice are very principled provisions, although detailed regulations on the use of sympathetic drugs have been issued, they have not yet come into effect. Due to the absence of detailed regulations, many issues such as the conditions of applicants and the approval procedure for compassionate use of drugs still need to be clarified. Since the use of compassionate drugs is in clinical trials that have not yet been approved for sale, and their safety and efficacy have not yet been finalized, their application should be very prudent.

Zhang Fang believes that in this epidemic, speeding up the market and compassion will be applied and how to be applied is very worthy of attention. If RIDGEVILLE proves its efficacy and value in a clinical trial for the treatment of new coronary pneumonia, it can not be ruled out in this outbreak, in order to save critically ill patients, in cases where regulations have yet to be perfected, first explore the practice of compassionate medication, expand to non-subjects in urgent need of patients, for the future provision of guidance or reference. This epidemic will promote and speed up the speed of drug marketing, compassion and other aspects of the landing and improvement of supporting regulations.
